Just because I haven't seen it mentioned yet, here's a solution using gcc's computed goto feature:<p><pre><code>  #include <cstdio>
  int main(int argc, char** argv) {
    void* labels[2] = { &&doing, &&done };
    int i = 1;
  doing:
    printf("%d
", i++);
    goto *labels[i / 1001];
  done:
    return 0;
  }
</code></pre>
Still consider goto harmful? (Well yeah, so do I generally. But hey...)
